{"type":"text","timestamp":1773352231369,"sessionID":"ses_31c036c7affe6dPx3n8MQ9tKUs","part":{"id":"prt_ce406c078001I68Xie8GidsIZb","sessionID":"ses_31c036c7affe6dPx3n8MQ9tKUs","messageID":"msg_ce406b445001u202eDyFh2U9g1","type":"text","text":"## Goal\n\nImplement a **dependency-aware sequential agent scheduling** feature for the `wombo-combo` AI agent orchestration system. This involves three subtasks:\n\n1. **Build dependency graph and detect cycles** (`dep-graph-builder`) - Parse `depends_on` fields across all features to build a DAG, detect circular dependencies, compute topological ordering\n2. **Sequential scheduling within dependency chains** (`dep-sequential-scheduler`) - When features A→B→C form a chain, schedule them sequentially in the same worktree with verification at each boundary\n3. **Diamond dependency merge gates** (`dep-diamond-merge-gates`) - When feature C depends on both A and B (different streams), C must wait until both are verified/merged\n\n## Instructions\n\n- **Dependency resolution must be fully programmatic** — no LLM/agent calls during execution. LLM decisions happen in the planning phase that produces `.features.yml`, not during execution.\n- Must handle diamond dependencies (feature C depends on both A and B from different streams)\n- Must detect circular dependencies and error before launching\n- Sequential features in the same chain should reuse the same worktree\n- Build verification must pass at each dependency boundary before the next feature starts\n- Must handle the case where a dependency fails (cancel downstream or re-queue)\n- **Do NOT invoke LLM/agent for dependency decisions** — this is pure graph scheduling\n- Use conventional commits: `feat(scope):`, `fix(scope):`, `refactor(scope):`, `docs(scope):`\n- Do NOT push to remote, do NOT modify `.features.yml`\n- Run `bun run build` to verify after all changes\n- The project uses Bun as its runtime and TypeScript\n\n## Discoveries\n\n- The codebase is a CLI tool (`wombo-combo`) that orchestrates AI agents for parallel feature development using git worktrees\n- **Feature model**: Features have `depends_on: string[]` fields already defined in the `Feature` and `Subtask` interfaces in `src/lib/features.ts`\n- **Existing dependency handling**: There's basic dependency checking in `features.ts` (`areDependenciesMet`, `getReadyFeatures`) that filters features by whether their deps are done, but no graph-based scheduling\n- **Existing graph visualization**: `src/commands/features/graph.ts` already has a cycle detection implementation for the `features graph` command, but it's visualization-only and not used for scheduling\n- **Launch flow**: `src/commands/launch.ts` → `cmdLaunch()` selects features via `selectFeatures()`, creates a `WaveState` with agents, then launches them. Now builds dep graph, validates, and creates schedule plan before creating agents.\n- **Worktree management**: `src/lib/worktree.ts` handles git worktree creation/cleanup. Chain features now share worktrees.\n- **State management**: `src/lib/state.ts` defines `WaveState` and `AgentState`. Agent statuses flow: `queued → installing → running → completed → verified → merged` (or `failed`/`retry`)\n- **Process monitoring**: `src/lib/monitor.ts` has `ProcessMonitor` class that tracks agent processes and fires callbacks on completion\n- **Build verification**: `src/lib/verifier.ts` runs build command in worktrees\n- **Merge handling**: `src/lib/merger.ts` handles merging feature branches, including conflict resolution\n- **Resume flow**: `src/commands/resume.ts` can resume interrupted waves — also updated with dep-aware scheduling\n- TypeScript strict mode is active — variables in recursive/self-referencing contexts need explicit type annotations to avoid circular inference errors\n- `bun run typecheck` runs `tsc --noEmit` and passes cleanly on all changes\n- Branch: `feature/dependency-aware-sequencing`\n\n## Accomplished\n\n### ✅ Completed: Subtask 1 — Dependency Graph Builder (`src/lib/dependency-graph.ts`)\n- Created `src/lib/dependency-graph.ts` with:\n  - `buildDepGraph()` — Constructs a DAG from features, building forward and reverse edges, detecting dangling deps\n  - `detectCycles()` — Iterative DFS with three-color marking (WHITE/GRAY/BLACK) for cycle detection\n  - `computeTopologicalOrder()` — Kahn's algorithm (BFS-based) for deterministic topological sorting\n  - `buildSchedulePlan()` — Groups features into parallel streams (linear chains) and identifies merge gates (diamond dependencies)\n  - `buildChainFrom()` — Follows single-successor paths to build linear chains for same-worktree reuse\n  - `validateDepGraph()` — Pre-launch validation that throws descriptive errors for cycles/dangling deps\n  - `areDepsReady()` — Runtime check if a feature's dependencies are all completed\n  - `formatSchedulePlan()` — Human-readable summary of the scheduling plan\n  - `getStreamForFeature()` — Lookup helper\n- **Committed**: `feat(dep-graph): add dependency graph builder with cycle detection and topological ordering`\n\n### ✅ Completed: Subtask 2 — Sequential Scheduling Within Dependency Chains\n- **State extensions** (`src/lib/state.ts`):\n  - Added `stream_index`, `depends_on`, `depended_on_by` fields to `AgentState`\n  - Added `schedule_plan` (`SerializedSchedulePlan`) to `WaveState`\n  - Added `areAgentDepsReady()` — checks if agent's deps are satisfied (verified/merged)\n  - Added `readyToLaunchAgents()` — dep-aware replacement for `queuedAgents()`\n  - Added `getDownstreamAgents()` — transitive downstream traversal\n  - Added `cancelDownstream()` — failure cascading to downstream agents\n  - **Committed**: `feat(dep-graph): add dependency tracking fields to WaveState and AgentState`\n\n- **Launch integration** (`src/commands/launch.ts`):\n  - `cmdLaunch` now builds dep graph, validates (errors on cycles/dangling), creates schedule plan\n  - Agent entries populated with `depends_on`/`depended_on_by`/`stream_index` from graph\n  - `launchNextQueued` uses `readyToLaunchAgents` (dep-aware)\n  - Added `launchAllReady()` — launches multiple unblocked agents after a dep completes\n  - `onComplete` callback uses `launchAllReady` instead of `launchNextQueued`\n  - `onError` callback cascades failures to downstream agents via `cancelDownstream()`\n  - Build failure at max retries cascades to downstream\n  - Dead process detection cascades failures to downstream\n  - **Committed**: `feat(dep-graph): integrate dependency-aware scheduling into launch and resume`\n\n- **Worktree reuse for chains** (`src/commands/launch.ts`):\n  - Features in the same chain (A→B→C) share the first feature's worktree path\n  - `launchSingleHeadless` detects chain reuse and does `git checkout -B` to switch branches\n  - Worktree cleanup skipped when downstream chain successors still need it (all 3 merge paths: clean, rebase, conflict resolution)\n  - **Committed**: `feat(dep-graph): support worktree reuse for sequential chains`\n\n- **Resume integration** (`src/commands/resume.ts`):\n  - Updated to import `launchAllReady`, `cancelDownstream`\n  - `onComplete`/`onError` use `launchAllReady` instead of `launchNextQueued`\n  - Dead process and conflict resolver death cascade failures\n\n### ✅ Completed: Subtask 3 — Diamond Dependency Merge Gates\n- Diamond deps naturally handled by `areAgentDepsReady` — C won't launch until ALL its deps (A and B) reach verified/merged\n- `launchAllReady` logs merge gate opening events when diamond-dep features become unblocked\n- **UI enhancements** (`src/lib/ui.ts`):\n  - Queued agents with deps show \"waiting: dep1, dep2\" in activity column\n  - Dashboard header shows stream/chain/merge gate counts from `schedule_plan`\n  - Dashboard summary shows merge gate status (waiting/ready/completed)\n- **Committed**: `feat(dep-graph): implement diamond dependency merge gates`\n\n### 🔲 Remaining: Final build verification\n- `bun run typecheck` passes ✅\n- **`bun run build` has NOT been run yet** — this is the final step required by the instructions\n- Need to verify the build succeeds and commit any fixes if needed\n\n## Relevant files / directories\n\n### Created\n- `src/lib/dependency-graph.ts` — DAG builder, cycle detection, topological sort, schedule planning, merge gates\n\n### Modified\n- `src/lib/state.ts` — Added `stream_index`, `depends_on`, `depended_on_by` to `AgentState`; added `schedule_plan`/`SerializedSchedulePlan` to `WaveState`; added dep-aware helpers (`areAgentDepsReady`, `readyToLaunchAgents`, `getDownstreamAgents`, `cancelDownstream`)\n- `src/commands/launch.ts` — Dep graph integration in `cmdLaunch`, dep-aware `launchNextQueued`/`launchAllReady`, chain worktree reuse in `launchSingleHeadless`, failure cascading in `onError`/`onComplete`/`handleBuildVerification`, worktree preservation for chain successors in `attemptMerge`\n- `src/commands/resume.ts` — Updated imports and callbacks to use `launchAllReady`/`cancelDownstream`\n- `src/lib/ui.ts` — Dep-aware dashboard: waiting status, schedule plan info, merge gate status display\n\n### Key reference files (read, not modified)\n- `src/lib/features.ts` — Feature types, `depends_on` field, `loadFeatures()`, `selectFeatures()`\n- `src/lib/launcher.ts` — Agent process spawning\n- `src/lib/monitor.ts` — `ProcessMonitor` class\n- `src/lib/verifier.ts` — `runBuild()`\n- `src/lib/merger.ts` — `mergeBranch()`, `mergeBaseIntoFeature()`\n- `src/lib/worktree.ts` — Git worktree lifecycle\n- `src/lib/prompt.ts` — Agent prompt generation\n- `src/lib/tui.ts` — TUI class\n- `src/config.ts` — `WomboConfig` type\n- `src/index.ts` — CLI entry point\n- `src/commands/features/graph.ts` — Existing graph visualization (separate from our implementation)\n- `package.json` — Build command: `bun build src/index.ts --outdir dist --target node`\n\n### Git state\n- Branch: `feature/dependency-aware-sequencing`\n- 5 commits made on this branch\n- All typecheck passes\n- **Next step**: Run `bun run build` to verify final build succeeds","time":{"start":1773352231368,"end":1773352231368}}}
